<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="602" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[2054,2649,2670,3087]" pageId="5" pageNumber="602">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1892" box="[2055,2260,2739,2773]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Acomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="602" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wilsoni">Acomys wilsoni</taxonomicName>
was formerly included in the 
<taxonomicName box="[2123,2332,2783,2812]" pageId="5" pageNumber="602">A. subspinosus</taxonomicName>
species group, and then genetic and molecular analyses found it to be a valid species, closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dollman" authorityYear="1911" box="[2182,2340,2897,2931]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Acomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="602" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percivali">A. percivali</taxonomicName>
. R. Matthey in 1968 found a chromosomal complement of 2n = 60 and FN = 76, and C. Fadda and colleagues in 2001 and M. Corti and colleagues in 2005 found 2n = 62 and FN = 76. The most recent molecular phylogeny revealed high diversity in Tanzania, and W. N. Verheyen and colleagues in 2011 found that 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Thomas" authorityYear="1892" box="[2299,2435,3132,3166]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Acomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="602" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wilson">A. wilson</taxonomicName>
: is probably a species complex based upon mtDNA sequences (cytochrome-b). Five subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
